#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Life Span"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Supatisutta → soppasisuttaṃ (bj) | suppatisuttaṃ (s1-3) | suppati (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Supatisutta"
msgstr "7. Sleeping"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.7:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn4.7:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bahudevarattiṃ abbhokāse caṅkamitvā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ "
"pāde pakkhāletvā vihāraṃ pavisitvā "
msgstr ""
"He spent most of the night practicing walking meditation in the open. At the "
"crack of dawn he washed his feet and entered his dwelling. "

msgctxt "sn4.7:1.3"
msgid ""
"dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi pāde pādaṃ accādhāya sato sampajāno "
"uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā."
msgstr ""
"He lay down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top "
"of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up."

msgctxt "sn4.7:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ soppasi kiṃ nu soppasi,"
msgstr "“What, you’re asleep? Really, you’re asleep?"

#. <br>
#. VAR: dubbhago → dubbhato (s1-3, km) | dubbhayo (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.2"
msgid "Kimidaṃ soppasi dubbhago viya;"
msgstr "You sleep like a loser—what’s up with that?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.3"
msgid "Suññamagāranti soppasi,"
msgstr "You sleep, thinking that the hut is empty."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.4"
msgid "Kimidaṃ soppasi sūriye uggate”ti."
msgstr "You sleep when the sun has come up—what’s up with that?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.1"
msgid "“Yassa jālinī visattikā,"
msgstr "“For them there is no craving—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhā natthi kuhiñci netave;"
msgstr "the weaver, the clinger—to lead them anywhere."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.3"
msgid "Sabbūpadhiparikkhayā buddho,"
msgstr "With the ending of all attachments the awakened Buddha sleeps."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.4"
msgid "Soppati kiṃ tavettha mārā”ti."
msgstr "What’s that got to do with you, Māra?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.7:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."
